name: Chocolate Zucchini Brownie Bites
author: Jane Ferrell Tippett
summary: Something different to do with an overabundance of zucchini. These brownie bites do not last long at my house. Store in an airtight container.
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Grease 3 mini muffin pans with cooking spray
Mix water and flax meal together and set aside until gelled, about 5 minutes
Mix flour and cocoa powder in a small bowl
Beat butter and sugar with an electric mixer in a large bowl until well combined
And 1/2 of the flax mixture and beat well
Add remaining flax mixture and vanilla extract; mix well
Blend in the flour mixture a little at a time until completely incorporated
Add zucchini with a spoon and mix well
Spoon batter into the prepared muffin pans
Bake in the preheated oven until edges pull away from the sides of the pan, about 20 minutes
Remove from the pans and cool on wire racks
